definition.value: Organ region, each instance of which has one or more anchored fiat boundaries.
An organ zone of the vagina.
Anatomical space which connects two or more compartment spaces or two or more anatomical cavities.
That portion of the body that lies between the thorax and the pelvis.

Subdivision of trunk proper, which is demarcated from the pelvis by the inferior surface of the pelvic diaphragm and from the lower limbs by the perineofemoral lines; together with the thorax, and abdomen, it constitutes the trunk proper.
The body region lying between the genital area and the anus on the surface of the trunk, and to the shallow compartment lying deep to this area that is inferior to the pelvic diaphragm.

A gland that surrounds the neck of the urinary bladder and the urethra. It secretes a substance that liquefies coagulated semen. It is situated in the pelvic cavity behind the lower part of the pubic symphysis, above the deep layer of the triangular ligament, and rests upon the rectum.
Lobular organ the parenchyma of which has as its parts glandular acini which are continuous with the prostatic part of the urethra.

The prostate gland is a partly muscular, partly glandular body that is situated near the base of the mammalian male urethra and secretes an alkaline viscid fluid which is a major constituent of the ejaculatory fluid.

The walnut shaped accessory sex gland of the reproductive system. It is located in the pelvis just below the bladder, surrounding the prostatic part of the urethra. The prostate gland secretes a fluid which is part of the semen.
In humans, one of the paired regions in the anterior portion of the thorax. The breasts consist of the mammary glands, the skin, the muscles, the adipose tissue, and the connective tissues.
One of two hemispheric projections of variable size situated in the subcutaneous layer over the pectoralis major muscle on either side of the chest.
Region of pectoral part of chest, each instance of which is the modified, glandular structure on some anterior chest and which has as its parts some nipple, areola, breast proper.
The upper ventral region of the torso of an organism.
Note that many transmasculine and nonbinary individuals use the term chest to refer to this area.
Anatomical boundary entity, each instance of which has one spatial dimension.
Anatomical boundary entity, each instance of which has zero spatial dimension.
Non-material anatomical entity of zero dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical line or surface.
Subdivision of cardinal body part which has as its direct part either upper or lower appendicular skeleton.
The distal extremity of the leg in vertebrates, consisting of the tarsus (ankle); metatarsus; phalanges; and the soft tissues surrounding these bones.

Material anatomical entity, each instance of which is either in fluid or solid state, with or without admixture of some cells and biological macromolecules; produced by some anatomical structures or derived from some inhaled or ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures.
Organ with organ cavity, each instance of which connects some renal sinus to some urinary bladder.
Distal free upper limb region, each instance of which consists of some carpus, metacarpus and set of digits.
The distal part of the arm beyond the wrist in humans and primates, that includes the palm, fingers, and thumb.
The distal portion of the upper extremity. It consists of the carpus, metacarpus, and digits.
An erectile structure homologous with the penis, situated beneath the anterior labial commissure, partially hidden between the anterior ends of the labia minora.
The erectile tissue in the vulva. It is composed of the corpora cavernosa and the glans clitoris.
Sometimes transgender people refer to their penis as a clitoris in order to reduce dysphoria associated with it.
A social entity pertains to the interaction among individuals and groups.
A social structure is a social entity which consists of relationships between two or more entities.
A disposition is the tendency of a capability to be exhibited under certain conditions or in response to a certain stimulus (trigger).
A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.
An information entity is an entity that represents information about some other entity. For example, a measurement, a clustered data set.
Information content entity is an object that requires some background knowledge or procedure to correctly interpret.
A function is a capability that satisfies some agentive objective, or (evolutionary) optimization.
An object quality is quality of an object.
A quantity is an informational entity that gives the magnitude of a property.
A measurement of a spatial location relative to a frame of reference or other objects.
A measurement value is a quantitative description that reflects the magnitude of some attribute.
A mathematical entity is an information content entity that are components of a mathematical system or can be defined in mathematical terms.
A plan is a set of intended actions, through which one expects to achieve a goal.
A language entity implements some language specification for the visual interpretation and is part of some document.
A visual language entity is a language entity that is manifested within the spectrum of light and can be pereceived and processed by a visual system.
A figure is a graphical entity which consists of a visual (n-dimentional) arrangement of information entities.
An image is an affine projection of a visual entity to a two dimensional surface.
A photograph is an image created by light falling on a light-sensitive surface.

Still image produced from radiation-sensitive materials (sensitive to light, electron beams, or nuclear radiation), generally by means of the chemical action of light on a sensitive film, paper, glass, or metal. Photographs may be positive or negative, opaque or transparent.

A specification is a description of the essential technical attributes/requirements for an object or procedure, and may be used to determine that the object/procedure meets its requirements/attributes.
An action specification is a specification composed of a sequence of instructions to achieve some objective.
A symbol is a proposition about what an entity represents.
An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.
A book is a publication composed of a large number of entries.
A volume made up of pages fastened along one edge and enclosed between protective covers.
A chapter is a document section of a book or thesis.
A novel is a fictitious prose narrative of book length, typically representing character and action with some degree of realism.

A novel is typically considered to be 40,000 words or longer (by the Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers of America). However, Smiley lists novels as between 100,000 and 175,000 words in length. National Novel Writing Month requires its novels to be at least 50,000 words.
A document section is a component of a document.

A capability is a realizable entity whose basis lies in one or more parts or qualities and reflects possibility of an entity to behave in a specified way under certain conditions or in response to a certain stimulus (trigger).
A sentence is a grammatical unit consisting of one or more words that bear minimal syntactic relation to the words that precede or follow it.
A word is the smallest free form (an item that may be expressed in isolation with semantic or pragmatic content) in a language.
Something that identifies or uniquely points to something or someone else.

A term used for identification. Names can identify a class or category of things, or a single thing, either uniquely, or within a given context. The entity identified by a name is called its referent.

A magazine is a periodical that typically contains essays, stories, poems, etc., by many writers, and often photographs and drawings, frequently specializing in a particular subject or area, as hobbies, news, or sports.
A description is language entity in which elements of a language (formal or natural) are used to characterize an entity.
A class is a collection of sets which can be unambiguously defined by a property that all its members share.
A list is any enumeration of a set of items.
A note is a brief document.
An article is a publication that is stand-alone section of a larger work.
Nonfictional prose forming an independent part of a publication.
A blog is a publication accessible at some website and is typically about various experiences.
